resources.string: The common Malaysian name for the timber of Ficus spp. (Moraceae). Vernacular names applied include arah (Sabah) and kayuara (Sabah). Major species include F. callosa, F. fistulosa, F. lamponga, F. magnoliifolia, F. microcarpa, F. racemosa, F. sundaica, F. superba, F. tinctoria, F. variegata, F. vasculosa, F. virens and F. viridicarpa. The sapwood is not differentiated from the heartwood, which is light yellow-brown or in various shades of yellow to pink-grey.Also known as Fig (India); Ara, Bunut, Karet and Kundang (Indonesia); Deua kiang, Mai deaua kham and Mai do (Laos); Nyaung (Myanmar); Papua New Guinea fig (Papua New Guinea);Balete (Philippines); Sai (Thailand); and Chi da and Sung (Vietnam).The common Malaysian name for the timber of Ficus spp. (Moraceae).
